1 C. Unless no economically practicable alternative is available,
2 plan assets shall not be entrusted to a fiduciary unless that
3 fiduciary has a practice of, and in writing commits to, following
4 guidelines, when engaging with portfolio companies and vote shares
5 or proxies that match the plan's obligation to act based only on
